eds help to rebuild. Vanguard News Nigeria A Taraba State socio-cultural group, the Taraba Peoples Assembly has condemned as wasteful spending, flamboyant celebration of Governor Dirus Dickson Ishaku's 100 days in offices, warning the governor to stop showcasing achievements of previous administration as his projects. September 8, 2015 In "News" Fortune often favours the enterprising; the trip to Abuja to obtain a copy of the Taraba State Tribunal judgment yielded an extra dividend. A chance meeting with Sylvanus Giwa, Senior Special Assistant to Governor Darius Dickson Ishaku, DDI, resulted in this interview. Giwa is a professional broadcaster. He started his… December 6, 2015 In "News" JALINGO—Governor Darius Ishaku of Taraba State, yesterday, pleaded with the Federal Government to refund to the state over N30 billion spent on rehabilitation of Federal roads by the previous administration of late the governor, Danbaba Suntai. August 25, 2017 In "News"